Or are you that in love with him, dumbass?

290
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,520
Sheesh. That's a fair point, Jettana.

291
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,560
- It wasn't a compliment.
- No, no, no.

292
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:42,040
You said he's only cute with me.

293
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,000
Gosh, you're so annoying.

294
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:45,040
Back to painting then.

295
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,360
Jamie is speechless.

296
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:50,680
He beat you at your game.

297
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,920
One to zero!

298
00:29:58,080 --> 00:30:00,400
- I'm just painting.
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

299
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:06,200
<i>I miss you so much.</i>

300
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:07,120
Guys.

301
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:10,080
Look at the camera. It's for my IG story.

302
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:38,880
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

303
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:46,720
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.

304
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:52,880
<i>Can you send me a selfie?</i>

305
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,160
Qin!

306
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,720
My cutie is calling.

307
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:50,080
Is there anything I can help you with?

308
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,080
<i>You can only look at it. No saving.</i>

309
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,800
It's too late now.

310
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:55,240
I already saved it.

311
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:57,840
Delete it.

312
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:58,760
<i>Hey.</i>

313
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:00,400
It's fire.

314
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:01,400
I'm keeping it.

315
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,800
I'll set it as my wallpaper.

316
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:04,280
Right.

317
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:05,560
I'll pay you to delete it.

318
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,920
What's your bank account?

319
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,080
I'll only accept ten kisses
per cheek as payment.

320
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,320
Then I'll delete.

321
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:13,920
Keep it then.

322
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:15,960
Yes!

323
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:17,360
You said it.

324
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:20,400
Are you back at your place?

325
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:23,360
I'm leaving soon.

326
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,440
<i>Get going then,</i>

327
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,480
<i>or you'll be late.</i>

328
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:29,640
If you don't want me to be late,
then stay with me.

329
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,920
Duang! You okay?

330
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:42,960
<i>Don't stress out over it</i>

331
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,480
<i>Don't care and be so serious</i>

332
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,800
Are you sure?

333
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,400
Just ignore him.

334
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,200
He's lost it.

335
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,200
See? He's beaming.

336
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,200
You…

337
00:32:58,280 --> 00:33:00,280
Are you trying to please me?

338
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:03,440
Please, my ass.

339
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:07,520
Okay, I'll stop.

340
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:08,680
Go see your friend.

341
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:11,120
Wait, don't hang up just yet.

342
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,040
Do you want anything from Bang Saen?

343
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:14,640
No.

344
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:16,440
You coming home safely is all I want.

345
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:21,640
Okay.

346
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:26,480
My body and my heart
will come home safely!

347
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:32,640
He hung up.

348
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:33,880
He hung up on me.

349
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,920
- He…
- Right.

350
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,440
- He…
- Get back to painting then.

351
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,160
The deadline is today.

352
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:40,800
Yeah.

353
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,719
Hey, guys!

354
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:43,719
I overheard Professor Phop
talking to a senior.

355
00:34:44,719 --> 00:34:45,840
And?

356
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:51,440
The professor said that
the jazz students have to host.

357
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:53,920
It's nothing new, is it?

358
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,639
The name of the event says it all.

359
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:58,440
I attended it a few years ago.

360
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:01,000
There were jazz performances
and a ton of food.

361
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,160
I know you already know all that.

362
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:08,520
But there's something
you still don't know.

363
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:09,800
And that is?

364
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:16,720
This year, there's a jazz contest.

365
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,840
Whoa. Sounds interesting.

366
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,120
Solo or band?

367
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,120
It has both.

368
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,520
Band contest.

369
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:25,720
I'm in.

370
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:26,680
- Deal.
- Deal!

371
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:32,520
I'll think about it.

372
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:34,520
Qin, you can't be like this.

373
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:36,800
You have to be the band's vocalist.

374
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:42,280
<i>For your singing technique,</i>

375
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:44,400
<i>you've already nailed it.</i>

376
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:46,840
But the emotion

377
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,760
isn't there yet.

378
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:51,800
I'm not up for it…

379
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:53,560
You're lying.

380
00:35:53,640 --> 00:35:54,960
Worrying about something?

381
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,400
Did someone insult you?

382
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,720
Nobody said anything.

383
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,280
I just don't want to do it.

384
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:08,840
Kim.

385
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:12,520
If Qin is out,

386
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:16,000
I guess we have to find a new vocalist.

387
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,160
No.

388
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,600
It has to be him.

389
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:22,840
Why look elsewhere
when our friend is so talented?

390
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:26,560
Yeah, you're right.

391
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,200
How about this?

392
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,000
Take time to think about it.

393
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,520
You've still got time.

394
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:35,920
I think you're just a bit tired.

395
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:39,280
Once you feel better,
come and say yes, all right?

396
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,760
Take your time.

397
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,120
I'm fucking stuffed.

398
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,480
I ate too much.

399
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:03,320
Well, it's only once in a while.

400
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:04,880
What do you mean?

401
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,280
We come here every week.

402
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,680
It's your favorite.

403
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:11,360
Qin.

404
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:13,120
Does something feel off?

405
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:14,800
What?

406
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:18,240
Duang hasn't been following
you around today.

407
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,560
Stop it already.

408
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:25,600
Okay, let's call it here, guys.

409
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,440
- Bye, Qin.
- Bye.

410
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:43,840
Qin.

411
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:12,800
Hi.

412
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:14,920
It's been a while.

413
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:19,240
By the way…

414
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,880
Are you going to watch
the junior marching band?

415
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,160
I don't know.

416
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,280
I have to go now.

417
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:32,960
Hey.

418
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,040
Was that Qin?

419
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:36,200
- Yeah, it was.
- What?

420
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:37,440
Hey! Hey! Hey!

421
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:38,640
Come here.

422
00:38:38,720 --> 00:38:39,560
Let's get dinner.

423
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:04,600
Hey, I'm back!

424
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:16,000
Hey.

425
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:18,120
Hey…

426
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:21,160
You're late.

427
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:24,360
You've been waiting for me?

428
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:26,320
No.

429
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,840
So stubborn.

430
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,840
Look!

431
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:34,600
I got you a souvenir.

432
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:47,840
Are you upset with me?

433
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:53,240
Wait…

434
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,160
You're burning up.

435
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,080
Did you take anything?

436
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:06,720
It's just the weather.

437
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,160
I'll be fine.

438
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:13,840
Take some medicine and then shower.

439
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,600
Go sit down.

440
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:16,600
I'll grab it for you.

441
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:23,200
You smell so nice.

442
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:25,000
You're burning up.

443
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:29,880
I already got better the moment I saw you.

444
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:34,280
Go sit down. I'll get you some medicine.

445
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:37,000
Fine.

446
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:40,080
I'll take some medicine.

447
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:56,240
<i>I'm happy we got to see each other.</i>

448
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:06,200
- Hey, I saw--
- Did you eat yet?

449
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,960
It's nothing.

450
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:12,040
It's just…

451
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,000
You rushing to get me medicine

452
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:19,320
means you missed me, right?

453
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,640
So did you eat yet?

454
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,400
I did.

455
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:38,840
I had dinner with Jamie and Pae.

456
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,200
What about you?

457
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,560
I did.

458
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:45,920
What did you have?

459
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:47,920
I went to Yang Noey.

460
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,320
You were there with

461
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:53,200
Tong, Kim,

462
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:56,560
and Cho, right?

463
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,000
Why do you ask?

464
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:02,200
Just Tong and Kim.

465
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:05,240
Take it and go shower.

466
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,480
This partner of mine is so sweet.

467
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:38,120
By the way, where do you want me
to hang the wind chime?

468
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,680
I'll find a spot for it.

469
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:44,600
No!

470
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:46,920
I'll do it.

471
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,200
No need.

472
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,160
Take a shower.

473
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:55,120
Right.

474
00:42:58,960 --> 00:42:59,960
Go!

475
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:08,960
HOW TO BRING DOWN A FEVER

476
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:14,080
HOME REMEDIES FOR A FEVER

477
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:15,720
1. DRINK A LOT OF WATER

478
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:17,280
2. WIPE DOWN WITH A DAMP CLOTH

479
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:25,560
Where are you going?

480
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:27,720
Stay in bed.

481
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:28,680
Don't get up.

482
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:30,120
I'll be back.

483
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:47,960
Take this
and let's go to the hospital.

484
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:54,400
This isn't a big deal.

485
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:56,440
It's not.

486
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:59,200
I'll get better after some sleep.

487
00:44:59,960 --> 00:45:00,840
Duang.

488
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:02,880
Can you not be stubborn?

489
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,480
I'm not.

490
00:45:07,080 --> 00:45:08,400
But I'm still fine.

491
00:45:10,360 --> 00:45:12,720
I only stayed out in the sun
for a bit too long.

492
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:18,320
Come sit here.

493
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:22,120
You already brought me water and medicine.

494
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:24,920
Do I have to take it now?

495
00:45:56,640 --> 00:45:58,360
<i>Why did you leave this part out?</i>

496
00:45:58,440 --> 00:45:59,760
<i>Why not layer them up properly?</i>

497
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,880
It wasn't me. It was you.

498
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:08,680
So it was you who did it.

499
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:32,320
Are you worried I'm going to die?

500
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:35,280
It's my bed.

501
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,560
Shouldn't I be worried?

502
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:41,200
Your lips are saying no again.

503
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:42,920
They're not.

504
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:55,760
Qin…

505
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:59,400
You're going to get sick too.

506
00:47:00,040 --> 00:47:00,920
So what?

507
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:02,680
You said it was nothing.

508
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:06,080
The one being stubborn

509
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:08,440
is none other than you.

510
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:13,320
Let me wipe you down.

511
00:47:17,920 --> 00:47:19,360
You know how to do it?

512
00:47:20,040 --> 00:47:21,040
I looked it up.

513
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:24,640
Genius.

514
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:51,880
I'm burning up.

515
00:47:58,640 --> 00:47:59,880
Feeling better yet?

516
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:23,200
Do you feel better?

517
00:48:24,280 --> 00:48:25,560
A whole lot better.

518
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:33,680
Thank you.

519
00:48:39,360 --> 00:48:40,440
Get well soon.

520
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:03,680
Duang, wake up.

521
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,080
Time for breakfast.

522
00:50:07,240 --> 00:50:08,880
I'm not hungry.

523
00:50:10,560 --> 00:50:11,440
Duang.

524
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:18,560
So strict.

525
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:21,040
I'm sick, okay?

526
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:22,320
Eat some breakfast

527
00:50:22,400 --> 00:50:23,560
and take your medicine.

528
00:50:27,720 --> 00:50:28,960
You're not going to feed me?

529
00:50:29,040 --> 00:50:30,560
Never.

530
00:50:33,160 --> 00:50:35,240
Please…

531
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:39,880
Open your mouth.

532
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,680
I don't feel like eating.

533
00:50:46,240 --> 00:50:47,960
I'm trying to feed you.
Have a little bit.

534
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:51,120
I want to cry.

535
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:53,760
Try to eat a little for me.

536
00:50:56,040 --> 00:50:57,320
Qin…

537
00:51:11,360 --> 00:51:12,320
One more.

538
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:13,440
Get it down.

539
00:51:13,520 --> 00:51:15,360
It's not tasty.

540
00:51:15,440 --> 00:51:17,400
It has to be. It's from your go-to place.

541
00:51:17,480 --> 00:51:18,880
No,

542
00:51:18,960 --> 00:51:20,240
you try it.

543
00:51:25,640 --> 00:51:26,840
For every bite you have,

544
00:51:26,920 --> 00:51:28,920
I'll give you a kiss.

545
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:31,640
Promise?

546
00:51:33,600 --> 00:51:35,080
Small bites, okay?

547
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:37,800
Hey.

548
00:51:37,880 --> 00:51:39,680
Can I ask you one more thing?

549
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:41,040
What is it?

550
00:51:42,560 --> 00:51:44,520
<i>Phodduang, nom, nom</i>

551
00:51:45,200 --> 00:51:47,240
<i>Nom, nom, good boy</i>

552
00:51:47,320 --> 00:51:49,840
<i>Good boy, nom, nom</i>

553
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:52,360
<i>Nom, nom, good job</i>

554
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:57,680
<i>Phodduang, nom, nom</i>

555
00:51:57,760 --> 00:51:59,600
<i>Nom, nom, good boy</i>

556
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:02,680
<i>Good boy, nom, nom</i>

557
00:52:07,560 --> 00:52:08,440
And then?

558
00:52:10,000 --> 00:52:11,720
You'll get all the kisses at once.

559
00:52:12,680 --> 00:52:15,240
No, you'll cheat.

560
00:52:32,560 --> 00:52:34,440
Refreshing.

561
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:41,720
Why are you staring at me?

562
00:52:43,120 --> 00:52:44,600
Because you're mine.

563
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:47,320
Right. I already know that.

564
00:52:49,120 --> 00:52:52,440
Did you know Jamie told me

565
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:55,360
I often tell people you're sweet,

566
00:52:56,680 --> 00:52:59,600
but you only act like that with me?

567
00:52:59,680 --> 00:53:01,840
He also said

568
00:53:01,920 --> 00:53:04,480
I love you way too much.

569
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:08,000
That's why I think you're the cutest.

570
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:12,000
He's not wrong.

571
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:15,920
Thank you for letting me take care of you.

572
00:53:17,680 --> 00:53:19,640
But right now,
I'm the one taking care of you.

573
00:53:25,640 --> 00:53:26,800
Sing it.

574
00:53:26,880 --> 00:53:28,560
<i>Phodduang, nom, nom</i>

575
00:53:28,640 --> 00:53:30,960
<i>Nom, nom, good boy</i>

576
00:53:31,040 --> 00:53:32,120
<i>Good boy, nom, nom</i>

577
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:33,200
Eat it.

578
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:38,640
With you taking care of me,

579
00:53:38,720 --> 00:53:39,880
I'll get better soon.

580
00:54:34,240 --> 00:54:35,400
Qin.

581
00:54:36,680 --> 00:54:37,680
What?

582
00:54:38,360 --> 00:54:40,120
Can I use your computer for a bit?

583
00:54:40,200 --> 00:54:43,080
I need to convert a file
and submit it to the professor.

584
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:45,120
Right. Go ahead.

585
00:54:55,640 --> 00:54:59,760
ON THIS DAY 2 YEARS AGO

586
00:55:03,120 --> 00:55:05,080
JUST FRIENDS BEING FRIENDLY

587
00:55:05,160 --> 00:55:06,480
TIW X QIN

588
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:08,240
MARCHING BAND KIDS DON'T DATE FRIENDS

589
00:55:15,160 --> 00:55:16,760
"Just friends being friendly."

590
00:55:18,600 --> 00:55:23,280
TIW X QIN

591
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:27,000
I'M HAPPY WE GOT TO SEE EACH OTHER.

592
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:02,960
Are you better now?

593
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:04,800
I am.

594
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:08,000
Should I order the usual?

595
00:56:09,360 --> 00:56:11,480
Garlic shrimp, stir-fried clams,

596
00:56:11,560 --> 00:56:13,200
cashew chicken, and porridge?

597
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:15,960
And…

598
00:56:16,960 --> 00:56:17,920
Spicy salted egg salad.

599
00:56:21,720 --> 00:56:23,080
You don't like that though.

600
00:56:25,320 --> 00:56:26,480
But you do.

601
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:31,280
You're so sweet.

602
00:56:36,600 --> 00:56:37,760
Auntie!

603
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:40,560
Here I am!

604
00:56:42,560 --> 00:56:44,160
What would you like to have?

605
00:56:46,720 --> 00:56:48,240
Garlic shrimp, stir-fried clams,

606
00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:50,720
cashew chicken,
spicy salted egg salad, and porridge.

607
00:56:51,560 --> 00:56:52,640
Can you repeat that?

608
00:56:52,720 --> 00:56:54,720
Garlic shrimp, stir-fried clams,

609
00:56:54,800 --> 00:56:57,080
cashew chicken,
spicy salted egg salad, and porridge.

610
00:56:57,160 --> 00:56:58,560
Okay, you remember, yeah?

611
00:56:58,640 --> 00:57:00,400
- Yes.
- Repeat one more time.

612
00:57:01,360 --> 00:57:02,360
Loud and clear.

613
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:05,360
Garlic shrimp, stir-fried clams,

614
00:57:05,440 --> 00:57:07,840
cashew chicken, spicy salted egg salad,
and porridge!

615
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:09,920
Hey, Chef! You got that?

616
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:10,920
Yes!

617
00:57:11,520 --> 00:57:12,440
Sit tight.

618
00:57:24,280 --> 00:57:25,680
Who are you texting?

619
00:57:29,920 --> 00:57:31,520
I wonder who it is…

620
00:57:33,160 --> 00:57:34,520
It's Tong.

621
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:38,160
Okay.

622
00:57:40,680 --> 00:57:41,920
Why? What is it?

623
00:57:42,440 --> 00:57:44,000
Nothing.

624
00:57:44,720 --> 00:57:47,400
I think we ordered a lot less today.

625
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:50,120
We usually order more.
I'm worried you won't be full.

626
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:52,840
Well…

627
00:57:52,920 --> 00:57:54,320
If not, we'll order more.

628
00:57:57,840 --> 00:57:58,680
Okay.

629
00:58:18,320 --> 00:58:19,920
Are you spoiling me?

630
00:58:21,880 --> 00:58:23,600
Ordering nothing but your favorites?

631
00:58:25,760 --> 00:58:26,760
I don't think I am.

632
00:58:27,560 --> 00:58:29,520
I want you to enjoy what you love.

633
00:58:29,600 --> 00:58:30,760
I want you to eat a lot.

634
00:58:31,480 --> 00:58:32,600
<i>Good boy, nom, nom</i>

635
00:58:32,680 --> 00:58:34,240
<i>Nom, nom, good boy</i>

636
00:58:34,320 --> 00:58:36,000
Was that an insult?

637
00:58:36,080 --> 00:58:37,480
Who would dare?

638
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:39,880
You're so tiny.

639
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:43,040
Stop it. You and that dirty mind of yours.

640
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:21,320
Duang.

641
00:59:27,920 --> 00:59:29,320
Yes? What is it?

642
00:59:30,160 --> 00:59:32,680
<i>Waiting for the wind</i>
<i>to carry me far and high</i>

643
00:59:32,760 --> 00:59:35,440
<i>So that I can fly before your eyes</i>

644
00:59:35,520 --> 00:59:37,920
<i>And see each other's hearts</i>

645
00:59:41,560 --> 00:59:44,280
<i>If you want me to be the stars</i>

646
00:59:44,360 --> 00:59:49,760
<i>All I can be is</i>
<i>a speck of dust flying far</i>

647
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:56,000
<i>If you want me to be the moon</i>

648
00:59:56,080 --> 01:00:02,760
<i>All I can be is a nobody</i>

649
01:00:03,560 --> 01:00:06,680
<i>I'm not the sky above</i>

650
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:09,520
<i>I can't reach</i>
<i>for the stars as you hoped</i>

651
01:00:09,600 --> 01:00:14,040
<i>All I can reach is mud and dirt</i>

652
01:00:15,640 --> 01:00:18,160
<i>I can be everything</i>

653
01:00:18,240 --> 01:00:20,920
<i>But what you've been wanting</i>

654
01:00:21,000 --> 01:00:23,840
<i>You're not to blame for not loving me</i>

655
01:00:27,080 --> 01:00:29,600
<i>I can be everything</i>

656
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:32,400
<i>But what you've been wanting</i>

657
01:00:32,480 --> 01:00:35,280
<i>You're not to blame for not loving me</i>

658
01:00:38,520 --> 01:00:40,560
<i>I can be everything</i>

659
01:00:40,640 --> 01:00:43,640
<i>But what you've been wanting</i>

660
01:00:43,720 --> 01:00:45,000
Duang.

661
01:00:45,840 --> 01:00:46,760
Duang!

662
01:00:48,800 --> 01:00:49,680
Do you like the song?

663
01:00:53,040 --> 01:00:53,960
What did you just say?

664
01:00:56,600 --> 01:00:58,200
I asked if you like the song.

665
01:00:59,760 --> 01:01:00,640
I do.

666
01:01:01,440 --> 01:01:02,880
And…

667
01:01:03,560 --> 01:01:05,080
Why did you tell me to listen to it?

668
01:01:07,920 --> 01:01:10,360
Well, it's… just a song I like.

669
01:01:26,080 --> 01:01:30,080
<i>Qin, you have to be here tomorrow!</i>
<i>Come watch the juniors' rehearsal.</i>

670
01:01:38,240 --> 01:01:41,160
Duang. Tomorrow, I'll be with
my high school friends.

671
01:01:42,040 --> 01:01:43,400
The marching band is rehearsing.

672
01:01:45,280 --> 01:01:46,160
Sure thing.

673
01:01:46,640 --> 01:01:47,880
Do you want me to drive you?

674
01:01:47,960 --> 01:01:50,240
Yes, of course.

675
01:01:51,480 --> 01:01:52,680
Can I pick you up too?

676
01:01:54,360 --> 01:01:55,320
Of course.

677
01:01:56,240 --> 01:01:58,040
Why are you asking these weird questions?

678
01:01:58,120 --> 01:01:59,440
Something on your mind?

679
01:02:28,920 --> 01:02:30,120
Pass it back, please.

680
01:02:35,840 --> 01:02:37,000
Whoa.

681
01:02:37,080 --> 01:02:37,920
Qin.

682
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:41,080
- At long last.
- Yeah.

683
01:02:41,160 --> 01:02:43,480
I'll take you to the juniors.

684
01:02:44,720 --> 01:02:47,280
- Come on.
- This marching band is amazing.

685
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:48,240
Qin.

686
01:02:48,840 --> 01:02:50,680
Tell me when you're done.

687
01:02:57,280 --> 01:02:58,280
The practice room.

688
01:02:58,360 --> 01:02:59,560
- Where?
- Way over there.

689
01:02:59,640 --> 01:03:01,000
- There?
- Right there.

690
01:03:06,920 --> 01:03:08,200
Can you stop talking nonsense?

691
01:03:08,280 --> 01:03:09,680
Hey! Wait up!

692
01:03:11,200 --> 01:03:13,280
Come on, Tiw! Cho is sweating bullets.

693
01:03:13,360 --> 01:03:14,560
Finally.

694
01:04:32,840 --> 01:04:34,440
Qin. Are we done?

695
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:35,760
I'm heading home.

696
01:04:37,600 --> 01:04:39,040
Hey.

697
01:04:39,720 --> 01:04:41,080
Now's the time.

698
01:04:42,640 --> 01:04:43,560
Go!

699
01:04:45,320 --> 01:04:46,360
Qin!

700
01:04:46,440 --> 01:04:47,360
Not you!

701
01:04:47,440 --> 01:04:48,440
- This way.
- Qin!

702
01:04:50,480 --> 01:04:51,320
Are you all right?

703
01:04:52,200 --> 01:04:53,640
I'm good.

704
01:04:54,440 --> 01:04:55,360
Qin.

705
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:57,440
Qin!

706
01:04:58,480 --> 01:04:59,520
Can we talk for a sec?

707
01:05:00,840 --> 01:05:01,680
Qin.

708
01:05:06,520 --> 01:05:07,840
You never replied.

709
01:05:10,080 --> 01:05:11,240
Are you in a relationship?

710
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:13,480
Why do you need to know?

711
01:05:15,760 --> 01:05:17,000
It's that guy, right?

712
01:05:18,960 --> 01:05:20,240
Just get to the point already.

713
01:05:21,920 --> 01:05:23,520
I just want to talk nicely.

714
01:05:25,520 --> 01:05:27,960
It's because of me, I know.

715
01:05:28,920 --> 01:05:30,120
I wasn't good to you.

716
01:05:52,280 --> 01:05:53,880
You're pretty good, you know?

717
01:05:53,960 --> 01:05:55,000
What's your name?

718
01:05:55,080 --> 01:05:55,960
I'm Tiw.

719
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:57,560
Qin.

720
01:05:58,320 --> 01:05:59,200
Qin?

721
01:06:00,120 --> 01:06:01,400
You like playing guitar?

722
01:06:01,480 --> 01:06:02,920
Oh, perfect timing.

723
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:05,240
My band needs another member.

724
01:06:05,320 --> 01:06:06,680
Care to join us?

725
01:06:06,760 --> 01:06:08,120
We can play together.

726
01:06:08,200 --> 01:06:09,880
We know each other?

727
01:06:09,960 --> 01:06:12,360
What? We do now.

728
01:06:13,000 --> 01:06:14,080
Come on, join us.

729
01:06:14,160 --> 01:06:15,200
Please, please, please.

730
01:06:16,800 --> 01:06:17,720
No.

731
01:06:23,520 --> 01:06:24,840
You don't want to join us

732
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:27,160
because you're worried I'll hit on you.

733
01:06:30,120 --> 01:06:30,960
Silence?

734
01:06:31,720 --> 01:06:33,320
That means I can make a move.

735
01:06:35,000 --> 01:06:36,240
Fine, fine.

736
01:06:36,320 --> 01:06:37,480
I'll stop.

737
01:06:37,560 --> 01:06:39,960
But please…

738
01:06:40,040 --> 01:06:41,280
Our band needs a guitarist.

739
01:06:41,360 --> 01:06:42,640
Please!

740
01:06:42,720 --> 01:06:43,600
Please…

741
01:07:01,920 --> 01:07:03,440
Qin! Here.

742
01:07:03,520 --> 01:07:04,600
I'll help.

743
01:07:04,680 --> 01:07:05,760
Hands off.

744
01:07:05,840 --> 01:07:07,160
I can carry it myself.

745
01:07:07,240 --> 01:07:08,200
Come on. Hand it over.

746
01:07:08,280 --> 01:07:09,600
There.

747
01:07:10,160 --> 01:07:11,080
Let this be my job.

748
01:07:12,040 --> 01:07:12,960
Come on.

749
01:07:17,640 --> 01:07:18,600
Whoa.

750
01:07:18,680 --> 01:07:20,080
You managed to get a new member?

751
01:07:20,720 --> 01:07:21,880
You're the real deal.

752
01:07:22,480 --> 01:07:24,320
That's too much of a tease, guys.

753
01:07:24,400 --> 01:07:27,280
I'm simply introducing you guys
to our new guitarist.

754
01:07:27,360 --> 01:07:28,720
Qin.

755
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:31,400
Allow me to officially introduce
my friends to you.

756
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:33,560
These two are my juniors.

757
01:07:33,640 --> 01:07:35,480
Boo is our drummer.

758
01:07:35,560 --> 01:07:36,760
That guy is Tum.

759
01:07:37,600 --> 01:07:39,640
And these two are my friends.

760
01:07:39,720 --> 01:07:41,120
That guy's name is Kie.

761
01:07:41,200 --> 01:07:42,320
As for that person…

762
01:07:42,400 --> 01:07:43,640
The name's Cho.

763
01:07:44,640 --> 01:07:45,640
There you have it.

764
01:07:45,720 --> 01:07:48,640
Now that we know each other, let's go!

765
01:07:48,720 --> 01:07:49,560
Time for practice.

766
01:07:49,640 --> 01:07:51,440
- It's time.
- How do we start…

767
01:07:51,520 --> 01:07:52,360
Let's practice!

768
01:07:52,440 --> 01:07:53,720
…while I restring my guitar.

769
01:07:54,960 --> 01:07:56,080
Try this, okay?

770
01:07:56,160 --> 01:07:57,120
Does it fit okay?

771
01:07:59,240 --> 01:08:00,200
Is it okay?

772
01:08:02,840 --> 01:08:03,840
Does it fit?

773
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:05,360
All good?

774
01:08:07,000 --> 01:08:08,080
Qin!

775
01:08:12,480 --> 01:08:13,720
You didn't wait for me.

776
01:08:14,440 --> 01:08:15,560
You're too slow.

777
01:08:15,640 --> 01:08:18,200
Yeah, it's my fault.

778
01:08:18,279 --> 01:08:20,560
Let me treat you to a meal, okay?

779
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:22,439
Trying to win me over with food?

780
01:08:24,200 --> 01:08:25,720
Is garlic shrimp enough?

781
01:08:27,080 --> 01:08:27,920
Yes.

782
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:30,439
As for the Americano…

783
01:08:31,319 --> 01:08:32,800
It's already getting late.

784
01:08:32,880 --> 01:08:33,840
It will keep you up.

785
01:08:34,560 --> 01:08:35,880
I'll get you a one tomorrow.

786
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:37,840
I can get one myself.

787
01:08:39,200 --> 01:08:40,200
No, don't!

788
01:08:40,960 --> 01:08:42,200
Let's just say…

789
01:08:42,920 --> 01:08:46,160
Can I be the one who buys you
an Americano every morning?

790
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:48,880
What if I say no?

791
01:08:48,960 --> 01:08:50,720
I'll buy you one anyway.

792
01:08:50,800 --> 01:08:52,319
Whatever floats your boat.

793
01:08:52,399 --> 01:08:53,319
Okay.

794
01:08:53,399 --> 01:08:55,080
Come on. It's garlic shrimp time.

795
01:08:55,160 --> 01:08:57,600
Let's go. Garlic shrimp time.

796
01:08:57,680 --> 01:08:58,680
Garlic shrimp time.

797
01:08:59,200 --> 01:09:01,080
Practice. Practice your delivery.

798
01:09:01,160 --> 01:09:02,160
How exactly?

799
01:09:02,240 --> 01:09:04,720
Well, you have to deliver it
nicely and clearly.

800
01:09:04,800 --> 01:09:06,880
Smile handsomely. Show me your smile.

801
01:09:08,399 --> 01:09:09,560
Wait, Cho…

802
01:09:10,279 --> 01:09:12,319
- You think he'll accept it?
- Of course he will!

803
01:09:12,399 --> 01:09:14,520
Trust me. This will work.

804
01:09:14,600 --> 01:09:15,680
Okay.

805
01:09:15,760 --> 01:09:16,840
Now, we wait.

806
01:09:16,920 --> 01:09:18,720
- Qin, this way.
- "Will you be my boyfriend?"

807
01:09:18,800 --> 01:09:19,880
- Quickly!
- And smile.

808
01:09:19,960 --> 01:09:20,960
Qin!

809
01:09:34,080 --> 01:09:34,960
What's this for?

810
01:09:37,080 --> 01:09:38,800
Oh, and…

811
01:09:40,200 --> 01:09:41,479
You're not going to accept it?

812
01:09:42,439 --> 01:09:43,279
Please accept it.

813
01:09:43,359 --> 01:09:45,080
Accept it! Accept it!

814
01:09:45,160 --> 01:09:46,080
Accept it!

815
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:48,000
Can we start talking?

816
01:10:00,680 --> 01:10:02,320
My friend is a boss.

817
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:03,360
Gosh, that was sweet.

818
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:05,400
You and your words. I'll see you in a bit.

819
01:10:05,480 --> 01:10:06,320
Qin!

820
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:07,440
Where's he going?

821
01:10:07,520 --> 01:10:08,560
Do we follow him?

822
01:10:08,640 --> 01:10:09,560
Of course.

823
01:10:09,640 --> 01:10:11,040
Go follow them!

824
01:10:21,600 --> 01:10:22,560
Can I go now?

825
01:10:23,400 --> 01:10:25,280
Can't we just talk nicely?

826
01:10:26,640 --> 01:10:27,960
How is this not talking nicely?

827
01:10:29,960 --> 01:10:31,400
So he's your boyfriend, correct?

828
01:10:34,520 --> 01:10:36,040
What's it to you?

829
01:10:36,680 --> 01:10:38,080
Just answer me.

830
01:10:39,000 --> 01:10:40,920
I'm trying to be nice here.

831
01:10:41,680 --> 01:10:43,000
Duang's not just a friend.

832
01:10:45,680 --> 01:10:46,720
Qin!

833
01:10:58,280 --> 01:10:59,680
Ready to go?

834
01:11:07,800 --> 01:11:08,720
Let's leave.

835
01:13:14,120 --> 01:13:15,440
Aren't you going to ask?

836
01:13:25,120 --> 01:13:26,400
You two were friends?

837
01:13:29,880 --> 01:13:30,880
Just friends.

838
01:13:33,360 --> 01:13:35,160
But he thought of me as more than that.

839
01:13:43,480 --> 01:13:45,480
We weren't really

840
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:48,800
in the talking stage either.

841
01:14:54,000 --> 01:14:56,000
You haven't talked to him since then?

842
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:02,720
When he confessed how he felt about me,

843
01:15:05,640 --> 01:15:07,720
I simply told him
I had good feelings towards him,

844
01:15:09,920 --> 01:15:12,320
but I didn't want
to advance the relationship.

845
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:17,120
Since then, we rarely talked,

846
01:15:20,080 --> 01:15:21,640
even though prior to this,

847
01:15:23,240 --> 01:15:24,640
we were always together.

848
01:15:29,800 --> 01:15:30,800
Was that mean?

849
01:15:33,720 --> 01:15:34,600
You were.

850
01:15:40,360 --> 01:15:42,960
But I never thought of you as a friend.

851
01:15:50,080 --> 01:15:53,080
We agreed we'd be in the talking stage.

852
01:16:58,640 --> 01:16:59,840
You're still upset?

853
